00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:26.040
YEN-JIE LEE: So what are
we going to do today?

00:00:26.040 --> 00:00:29.990
So today, we're going to
continue the discussion,

00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:35.080
based on what we have learned
from the diffraction and also

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:36.530
other interesting phenomena.

00:00:36.530 --> 00:00:38.660
And we are going
to make connections

00:00:38.660 --> 00:00:44.030
to quantum mechanics
and discuss in greater

00:00:44.030 --> 00:00:46.730
detail about this connection.

00:00:46.730 --> 00:00:49.550
And also, if time
allows, we are going

00:00:49.550 --> 00:00:58.650
to cover information about
gravitational waves as well.

00:00:58.650 --> 00:01:02.750
So last time, we have
discussed diffraction pattern

00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:04.790
coming from a laser beam.

00:01:04.790 --> 00:01:08.540
And we discussed
about resolution.

00:01:08.540 --> 00:01:11.940
And you can see that this is the
graph we see, last time already

00:01:11.940 --> 00:01:13.190
in the lecture.

00:01:13.190 --> 00:01:15.860
Basically, all the
point light source

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:23.300
coming through a single slit is
going to be doing interference

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:24.540
to each other.

00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:27.530
So basically, you see
interesting pattern,

00:01:27.530 --> 00:01:32.060
which you have a central peak.

00:01:32.060 --> 00:01:35.780
And the total constructing
for interference

00:01:35.780 --> 00:01:39.680
happens at the
center of the screen.

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:43.550
And at some point,
you have a deep--

00:01:43.550 --> 00:01:48.330
which is actually where total
destructive interference

00:01:48.330 --> 00:01:49.450
actually happened.

00:01:49.450 --> 00:01:53.570
And we were able to understand
this with mathematics,

00:01:53.570 --> 00:01:56.490
which we learned in 18.03.

00:01:56.490 --> 00:01:58.550
Another interesting
result we find

00:01:58.550 --> 00:02:02.780
is that, if we shoot a
laser beam to the moon--

00:02:02.780 --> 00:02:06.290
by now, you should be able to
conclude that it's not going

00:02:06.290 --> 00:02:09.650
to be a point on the moon.

00:02:09.650 --> 00:02:15.140
Instead, it's going to be a spot
as large as the whole Missouri

00:02:15.140 --> 00:02:16.460
state.

00:02:16.460 --> 00:02:19.620
So that's actually
another interesting result

00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:23.880
we found from that
discussion last time.

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:27.080
And finally, we are
able to put together

00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:30.320
all the things we have learned
from the last few lectures.

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:34.200
Basically, you can
have, at the same time,

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:38.910
the effect of multi-slit
interference and also

00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:41.900
the effect of a single
slit diffraction--

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:43.760
all then put together.

00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:47.960
Then you have this complicated
but also beautiful pattern,

00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:50.510
which you will be able
to observe on the screen.

00:02:50.510 --> 00:02:55.040
And basically, the point is
that you are going to have,

00:02:55.040 --> 00:02:59.670
for example, in this case,
five-slit interference pattern.

00:02:59.670 --> 00:03:02.110
But that is actually modulated.

00:03:02.110 --> 00:03:05.660
The intensity is
modulated by the pattern

00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:09.280
from a single-slit diffraction.

00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:12.650
OK, so that is
actually what we have

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:16.070
learned from the last lecture.

00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:25.370
Coming back to the original
question, why do we study 8.03?

00:03:25.370 --> 00:03:30.890
The reason is that we
would like to understand--

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:35.250
we would like to hear
from that universe.

00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:38.800
So we cannot even
recognize the universe,

00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:42.090
without using waves
and vibrations.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:46.460
So that's the course in which
we have been doing here.

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:50.010
And we have seen
waves of matter.

00:03:50.010 --> 00:03:54.920
So for example, here, we have
this water wave generator.

00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:56.450
You can see water waves.

00:03:56.450 --> 00:03:59.120
We have this Bell Lab machine.

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:03.320
Because you can see the
coupled oscillator--

00:04:03.320 --> 00:04:05.540
a multiple coupled oscillator.

00:04:05.540 --> 00:04:08.090
And they are doing
their job together

00:04:08.090 --> 00:04:10.190
to form beautiful waves.

00:04:10.190 --> 00:04:15.050
And you can see those
beautiful results from there.

00:04:15.050 --> 00:04:19.980
Last time and also including
the last few lectures,

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:23.120
we have been using
this laser to produce

00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:27.110
interesting interference
patterns and the diffraction

00:04:27.110 --> 00:04:28.910
pattern.

00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:32.720
So that's the second kind
of wave, which we encounter.

00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:36.600
The first kind is
the waves of matters.

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:39.660
The second kind
is waves of what?

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:42.930
Waves of vector fields.

00:04:42.930 --> 00:04:44.570
It's not matter anymore.

00:04:44.570 --> 00:04:48.830
Because this field,
this oscillation field,

00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:51.630
can also travel through vacuum.

00:04:51.630 --> 00:04:53.600
So that is actually
the second kind

00:04:53.600 --> 00:04:59.660
of wave, which we
should learn for 8.03.

00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:05.090
They provide a pretty
adequate description

00:05:05.090 --> 00:05:08.270
of the nature, description
of the phenomenon, which

00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:12.890
we can actually measure, and
see from the experiment we

00:05:12.890 --> 00:05:15.120
went over.

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:19.640
So what I would like to
say in the lecture today

00:05:19.640 --> 00:05:25.310
is that there are two kinds
of completely different waves,

00:05:25.310 --> 00:05:27.750
which we haven't talked about.

00:05:27.750 --> 00:05:32.450
The first one is the
probability density wave,

00:05:32.450 --> 00:05:36.230
which I will cover
that in a few moments.

00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:40.010
The second one is
gravitational waves.

00:05:40.010 --> 00:05:43.940
This is actually a
space-time distortion

00:05:43.940 --> 00:05:48.830
coming from the motion
of massive objects.

00:05:48.830 --> 00:05:51.490
And we would like to
see what we can also

00:05:51.490 --> 00:05:55.100
learn from there, using the
existing knowledge of which we

00:05:55.100 --> 00:05:59.530
have learned from matter waves
and the vector-field waves.

00:05:59.530 --> 00:06:02.970
And that they are, actually,
pretty similar to each other

00:06:02.970 --> 00:06:06.210
if you look at their behavior.

00:06:06.210 --> 00:06:12.220
So the first thing which I
would like to discuss is light.

00:06:12.220 --> 00:06:16.260
So far, what is light?

00:06:16.260 --> 00:06:20.630
Light is like
electromagnetic waves.

00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.530
So that is actually
what we have learned

00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:25.530
so far from 8.02 and 8.03.

00:06:25.530 --> 00:06:27.210
So they are like waves.

00:06:27.210 --> 00:06:29.670
They are waves, all right.

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:34.290
On the other hand,
in the 20th century,

00:06:34.290 --> 00:06:38.050
there are many, many
crises going on.

00:06:38.050 --> 00:06:40.260
So the first thing
which is happening

00:06:40.260 --> 00:06:43.900
is photoelectric effect.

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:48.270
So this experimental
result was actually

00:06:48.270 --> 00:06:52.290
first discovered by Hertz.

00:06:52.290 --> 00:06:57.390
So he found that, if you
want to kick one electron out

00:06:57.390 --> 00:07:01.960
of some material or
some charged material,

00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:08.160
it is easier if you use a
high-frequency light compared

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:10.470
to low-frequency light.

00:07:10.470 --> 00:07:11.430
So that's the issue--

00:07:11.430 --> 00:07:12.840
really strange.

00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:17.880
Because based on waves and
also the intensity formula--

00:07:17.880 --> 00:07:21.270
while we really
care, intensity is

00:07:21.270 --> 00:07:25.580
proportional to the square of
the electric field amplitude.

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:28.110
So that's actually
what we learned

00:07:28.110 --> 00:07:30.070
from the previous lectures.

00:07:30.070 --> 00:07:35.100
But what Hertz was saying
is that the frequency also

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:36.300
matters.

00:07:36.300 --> 00:07:40.710
OK, so that's really
a bit strange.

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:44.780
And Einstein actually
came in and explained

00:07:44.780 --> 00:07:48.120
this photoelectric effect.

00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:51.510
So what we found
is that this effect

00:07:51.510 --> 00:08:01.950
can be explained by viewing
the light of small quantas.

00:08:01.950 --> 00:08:07.780
And light is actually
not like waves any more,

00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:09.950
but like quantas--

00:08:09.950 --> 00:08:12.540
the small quantas--
discrete ones--

00:08:12.540 --> 00:08:18.470
with energy proportional
to the frequency.

00:08:18.470 --> 00:08:20.020
All right?

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:25.380
And basically, the energy
of those little quanta--

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:28.440
or we now call them photons--

00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:35.370
is actually equal to h,
which is some constant--

00:08:35.370 --> 00:08:41.100
relate the frequency and
the energy of the quanta.

00:08:41.100 --> 00:08:45.570
And with this
explanation, the view

00:08:45.570 --> 00:08:50.250
is that the photons
are like particles.

00:08:50.250 --> 00:08:53.940
And therefore, he can
actually explain that, OK,

00:08:53.940 --> 00:09:02.530
if I measure the kinetic energy,
the maxima kinetic energy

00:09:02.530 --> 00:09:09.900
of the electrons,
which are kicked out

00:09:09.900 --> 00:09:14.820
from this photoelectric
effect experiment.

00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:16.255
I call it K-max.

00:09:19.420 --> 00:09:23.230
What you are going to get
is a formula like this.

00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:26.850
The maxima kinetic
energy of electrons

00:09:26.850 --> 00:09:34.120
will be equal to h
bar mu minus phi.

00:09:34.120 --> 00:09:37.110
Phi is actually some
kind of threshold,

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:39.450
which you need
or, say, some kind

00:09:39.450 --> 00:09:42.420
of energy, which you need
to overcome to kick one

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:47.070
electron out of the material.

00:09:47.070 --> 00:09:52.860
So you can see from here that,
if the frequency of the light

00:09:52.860 --> 00:09:56.660
is too low, then
this will never work.

00:09:56.660 --> 00:10:01.460
Because the maximum kinetic
energy will be below 0.

00:10:01.460 --> 00:10:06.170
Therefore, you cannot
kick out a electron.

00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:12.950
But if the frequency is high,
as shown by Hertz experiment,

00:10:12.950 --> 00:10:13.982
it is possible.

00:10:13.982 --> 00:10:20.300
And also, you can create
energetic electron,

00:10:20.300 --> 00:10:23.240
have them kicked
out of the material.

00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:26.730
And this is actually
verified by experiment.

00:10:26.730 --> 00:10:29.990
And that's essentially
why Einstein should

00:10:29.990 --> 00:10:33.860
get the Nobel Prize in 1921.

00:10:33.860 --> 00:10:38.260
So let me tell you
what the feeling here--

00:10:38.260 --> 00:10:42.340
the feeling here is that, now,
things are really becoming

00:10:42.340 --> 00:10:43.570
more and more interesting.

00:10:43.570 --> 00:10:46.330
Because first of
all, we see really

00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:51.310
well that the electromagnetic
wave describes

00:10:51.310 --> 00:10:53.240
the behavior of the light.

00:10:53.240 --> 00:10:54.270
We see diffraction.

00:10:54.270 --> 00:10:56.190
We see interference.

00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:57.910
All those things
can be explained

00:10:57.910 --> 00:11:02.380
by the beautiful mathematics,
which we have been employing

00:11:02.380 --> 00:11:04.270
to explain all those results.

00:11:04.270 --> 00:11:07.870
But here, you can see
that, at the same time,

00:11:07.870 --> 00:11:15.730
the photons are very good
tool or very good viewpoint

00:11:15.730 --> 00:11:18.280
to explain the
photoelectric effect.

00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:24.130
So that's actually
really surprising.

00:11:24.130 --> 00:11:27.430
Because that means
you have, suddenly,

00:11:27.430 --> 00:11:30.860
both kinds of explanation
of light, which should

00:11:30.860 --> 00:11:34.240
be describing the same thing.

00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:39.050
So now, one idea is to
describe them by waves.

00:11:39.050 --> 00:11:43.390
The other idea is to
describe them by particles.

00:11:43.390 --> 00:11:45.740
And also, at the same
time, as we actually

00:11:45.740 --> 00:11:48.820
discussed in the
previous lecture,

00:11:48.820 --> 00:11:55.930
we can do a two-slit
experiment with billiard balls

00:11:55.930 --> 00:11:58.720
or with bullets.

00:11:58.720 --> 00:12:01.530
Suppose we do this experiment.

00:12:01.530 --> 00:12:08.900
We fire the balls or
bullets through some source.

00:12:08.900 --> 00:12:16.100
And we have some kind
of two-slit set up here,

00:12:16.100 --> 00:12:20.060
so that the bullets or balls
can actually pass through.

00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:21.880
And then we were
wondering, what will

00:12:21.880 --> 00:12:25.270
be the pattern which we
see from the detector

00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:27.230
in the right-hand side.

00:12:27.230 --> 00:12:29.610
And basically, what we
see is the following.

00:12:29.610 --> 00:12:31.910
So basically, we
have a distribution

00:12:31.910 --> 00:12:39.800
of the balls coming
from slit number one.

00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:44.750
And we have another distribution
of balls, which is actually

00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:48.230
coming from slit number two.

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:52.220
And I can call it P-1 and
P-2, which is actually

00:12:52.220 --> 00:12:55.940
the probability
density distribution

00:12:55.940 --> 00:12:58.350
of the experimental result.

00:12:58.350 --> 00:13:03.350
And the final result,
or say, if you just

00:13:03.350 --> 00:13:05.920
look at the
distribution of balls

00:13:05.920 --> 00:13:11.990
without separating the
balls from slit number

00:13:11.990 --> 00:13:14.810
one and slit number
two, basically you

00:13:14.810 --> 00:13:18.320
get some distribution
like this, which

00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:23.750
is a superpositional P-1
and the P-2 distributions.

00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:28.530
All of these things
doesn't surprise anybody.

00:13:28.530 --> 00:13:34.540
The experiment one,
which we perform--

00:13:34.540 --> 00:13:41.130
now, instead of billiard balls,
we perform the same experiment

00:13:41.130 --> 00:13:44.380
with electrons.

00:13:44.380 --> 00:13:47.230
And again, we have
all those electrons

00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:53.790
pass through this two-slit
two-slit experiment.

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:58.390
As we see before,
basically, again, we

00:13:58.390 --> 00:14:04.060
can actually separate electrons
from the first slit, which

00:14:04.060 --> 00:14:12.220
I called I-1, and the
intensity of electrons

00:14:12.220 --> 00:14:16.840
coming from the second
slit, which I called I-2.

00:14:16.840 --> 00:14:20.510
Then, basically, if you
can identify and make sure

00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:22.990
that the electron is coming
from one of the slits,

00:14:22.990 --> 00:14:26.910
you are going to get
distribution like this.

00:14:26.910 --> 00:14:28.000
OK?

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:33.790
And of course, I can always
write these I-1 as a sine wave

00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:37.480
function, psi-1 squared.

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:41.280
And I can always write this
I-2, which is the intensity

00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:45.610
as a function of position of the
electron coming from the second

00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:46.870
slit--

00:14:46.870 --> 00:14:50.580
I can always write
it as psi-2 squared.

00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:56.980
In the case of
light, it's actually

00:14:56.980 --> 00:15:02.380
just proportional to
the electric field.

00:15:02.380 --> 00:15:06.520
So if you accept this,
and now you actually

00:15:06.520 --> 00:15:10.620
don't measure where
the electron actually

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:14.050
pass through when the
electron from the source

00:15:14.050 --> 00:15:15.910
passed through this experiment--

00:15:15.910 --> 00:15:20.650
we now don't measure if it
passed through one or two.

00:15:20.650 --> 00:15:23.850
Then, the pattern
becomes like this.

00:15:23.850 --> 00:15:29.690
You have something like
this which, essentially,

00:15:29.690 --> 00:15:35.860
is very, very similar to
the two-slit interference

00:15:35.860 --> 00:15:42.190
experimental result of
the laser experiment.

00:15:42.190 --> 00:15:46.570
As you see from this
experimental result,

00:15:46.570 --> 00:15:50.480
you see some kind of pattern.

00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:52.300
You have the peak.

00:15:52.300 --> 00:15:54.570
You have the valley,
as a function

00:15:54.570 --> 00:15:57.470
of position in the detector.

00:15:57.470 --> 00:16:02.590
And we can actually call
this I-1-2, which is actually

00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:08.320
when you don't measure
or you don't identify

00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:11.600
which slit the
electron goes through,

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:14.740
then you have the intensity,
which is actually called I-1-2.

00:16:17.330 --> 00:16:22.400
And what we actually found
is that I-1-2 is actually

00:16:22.400 --> 00:16:26.890
not I-1 plus I-2.

00:16:26.890 --> 00:16:32.020
What we found is that
I-1-2 is actually psi-1

00:16:32.020 --> 00:16:34.045
plus psi-2 squared.

00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:43.000
So basically, we see
interference pattern.

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:49.952
And this will be equal to I-1
plus I-2 plus 2 squared root

00:16:49.952 --> 00:16:55.840
of I-1 plus I-2 and
the cosine delta,

00:16:55.840 --> 00:17:03.170
where the delta is coming from
the path length difference.

00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:07.490
So based on this
experimental result,

00:17:07.490 --> 00:17:10.609
this is actually
really surprising.

00:17:10.609 --> 00:17:16.829
First of all, electrons are
arriving like a particle,

00:17:16.829 --> 00:17:17.329
right?

00:17:17.329 --> 00:17:20.869
Because we can see
from this slide,

00:17:20.869 --> 00:17:26.662
if you look at the upper left
figure, you see doo-doo-doo.

00:17:26.662 --> 00:17:31.010
Every time, you have
something hitting the screen.

00:17:31.010 --> 00:17:33.160
And what is actually left over?

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:37.260
It's a single hit on the screen.

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:43.190
Therefore, the electrons are
arriving like a particle,

00:17:43.190 --> 00:17:46.250
producing a hit in the detector.

00:17:46.250 --> 00:17:49.760
On the other hand,
what we are saying here

00:17:49.760 --> 00:17:56.420
is that, before
they hit the screen,

00:17:56.420 --> 00:17:59.800
they are behaving like a wave.

00:17:59.800 --> 00:18:03.940
It has interference with
itself, like a wave.

00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:07.310
All right, so is
electron a particle?

00:18:07.310 --> 00:18:09.845
Or is the electron a wave?

00:18:15.120 --> 00:18:17.130
Strange.

00:18:17.130 --> 00:18:20.490
The answer is
electron is actually

00:18:20.490 --> 00:18:22.225
