00:25:20.830 --> 00:25:23.410
of individual photons?

00:25:23.410 --> 00:25:25.610
How do I do that?

00:25:25.610 --> 00:25:31.440
What I could do is to
lower the frequency

00:25:31.440 --> 00:25:35.700
of the electromagnetic
wave of the light source

00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:40.380
or, say, increase
the wavelengths

00:25:40.380 --> 00:25:41.850
of the light source.

00:25:41.850 --> 00:25:45.090
OK, this is very nice.

00:25:45.090 --> 00:25:47.640
Because now, I can
keep this in, right?

00:25:47.640 --> 00:25:50.340
So that I make sure
all the electrons

00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:54.660
are bothered by the photon.

00:25:54.660 --> 00:25:57.310
Because I can emit
very high rate.

00:25:57.310 --> 00:26:00.850
But at the same time, I can
also lower the intensity,

00:26:00.850 --> 00:26:04.920
so that the intensity
